---
// TEMPLATE DRAFT — NOT LEGAL ADVICE.
// This Privacy Policy was generated as a first-draft starting point based on
// what this codebase actually does (Wix Stores/eCom checkout, Wix Contacts
// newsletter signup, a single first-party cart-session cookie, no analytics
// or advertising trackers as of this writing). The store owner must review
// this with a qualified attorney before launch to confirm it is accurate,
// complete, and compliant with applicable law (e.g. CCPA/CPRA for California
// residents, GDPR if serving the EU/UK, COPPA, state privacy laws, etc.)
// before relying on it. Bracketed placeholders below must be filled in.
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Icon from '../components/Icons.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'July 2, 2026';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy" description="How PawVault collects, uses, and protects your personal information.">
  <div class="page-inner">

    <div class="page-hero">
      <div class="hero-badge">
        <Icon name="lock" size={13} color="#2D6A4F" aria-hidden={true} />
        <span>Legal</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      <p class="intro">
        This policy explains what personal information PawVault ("we," "us," or "our") collects when you visit
        or shop at this site, how we use it, and who we share it with. If you have questions, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:hello@pawvault.com">hello@pawvault.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-body">

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
        <p>We collect information in the following ways:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Order information.</strong> When you place an order, we collect your name, email address,
            shipping address, billing address, phone number (if provided), and the details of what you purchased.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Payment information.</strong> Checkout is processed through Wix's payment infrastructure and
            payment providers. We do not receive or store your full card number or other complete payment
            credentials — that information goes directly to Wix and its payment partners.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Newsletter signups.</strong> If you submit your email through our newsletter form, we add it
            to our contacts list (hosted on Wix's Contacts platform) so we can send you the emails you signed up
            for. We do not collect anything else through that form.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Communications.</strong> If you email us or otherwise contact us directly, we keep a record
            of that correspondence so we can respond to you and follow up if needed.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>2. Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
        <p>
          This site uses one first-party cookie that we set directly: a cart-session identifier that lets your
          shopping cart persist as you move between pages. It's required for the cart and checkout to function
          and doesn't track you across other websites.
        </p>
        <p>
          As of this writing, this site does not use analytics, advertising, or third-party tracking cookies. If
          that changes in the future, we will update this policy to describe what's added and, where required by
          law, request your consent first.
        </p>
        <p>
          Separately, Wix — the platform we use to host this site, run our store, and process payments — may set
          its own cookies needed to operate the site, complete transactions, and prevent fraud. Those are governed
          by Wix's own privacy practices, not this policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>3. How we use your information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To process, fulfill, and ship your orders, and to communicate with you about order status.</li>
          <li>To send marketing emails if you've opted in via our newsletter — you can unsubscribe at any time.</li>
          <li>To respond to customer service requests, questions, and return or refund requests.</li>
          <li>To calculate applicable sales tax and shipping costs at checkout.</li>
          <li>To maintain the security of our store and prevent fraud.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>4. Who we share your information with</h2>
        <p>We don't sell your personal information. We share it only as needed to run the store:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Wix.</strong> Our website, product catalog, cart, checkout, payment processing, and contacts
            list all run on Wix's platform, so Wix processes the information described above on our behalf.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Order fulfillment suppliers.</strong> Our products are sourced and shipped by third-party
            suppliers. When you place an order, we share the information needed to fulfill and ship it — your
            name, shipping address, and order contents — with the supplier responsible for that product. We do
            not share your payment details with suppliers.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Payment providers.</strong> Payment and billing details you enter at checkout go directly to
            Wix's payment processing partners to complete your transaction.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Legal requirements.</strong> We may disclose information if required to by law, or to protect
            the rights, property, or safety of PawVault, our customers, or others.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>5. Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          We keep order and contact information for as long as needed to fulfill the purposes described in this
          policy, and as required to meet our legal, tax, and accounting obligations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>6. Your choices and rights</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You can unsubscribe from marketing emails at any time using the link in any email we send, or by contacting us.</li>
          <li>
            Depending on where you live, you may have the right to request access to, correction of, or deletion
            of your personal information. To make a request, email us at
            <a href="mailto:hello@pawvault.com">hello@pawvault.com</a> and we'll respond as required by applicable law.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          This site is intended for adults and is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
          personal information from children.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>8. Security</h2>
        <p>
          Checkout on this site runs through Wix's SSL-encrypted infrastructure. No method of transmission or
          storage is completely secure, but we rely on Wix's platform-level security practices to help protect
          your information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with a revised
          "Last updated" date above.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="legal-section">
        <h2>10. Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy or your personal information? Email
          <a href="mailto:hello@pawvault.com">hello@pawvault.com</a>.
        </p>
        <p class="placeholder-note">[Business legal name and mailing address to be added here]</p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root {
    --green: #2D6A4F;
    --cream: #FFF9F0;
    --terra: #C9663C;
    --dark: #0F1117;
    --gray: #6B7280;
    --border: #E8E3DB;
  }

  .page-inner { max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 64px 24px 96px; }

  .page-hero { margin-bottom: 48px; }
  .hero-badge {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 6px;
    background: rgba(45,106,79,0.07);
    color: var(--green);
    padding: 5px 12px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .page-hero h1 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    color: var(--dark);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .last-updated {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .intro { font-size: 1rem; color: #4B5563; line-height: 1.7; }
  .intro a { color: var(--green); font-weight: 500; }

  .legal-body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 40px; }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    color: var(--dark);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    padding-bottom: 12px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .legal-section p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #4B5563;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  .legal-section p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .legal-section a { color: var(--green); font-weight: 500; }

  .legal-section ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
  }
  .legal-section li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: #4B5563;
    line-height: 1.75;
    padding-left: 20px;
    position: relative;
  }
  .legal-section li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 4px;
    top: 10px;
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--green);
  }
  .legal-section strong { color: var(--dark); font-weight: 600; }

  .placeholder-note {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--terra);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page-inner { padding: 48px 20px 72px; }
  }
</style>
